text: Erle () is a rural locality (a settlement) in Yaksatovsky Selsoviet, Privolzhsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 79 in 2010. There are three streets. == Geography == It is located on the Kigach River. == References == Category:Rural localities in Privolzhsky District, Astrakhan Oblast
title: Erle, Astrakhan Oblast
